cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper proposes the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) to improve sonar image matching, which is a problem in robotics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper focuses on Autonomous Underwater Vehicles, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning also indicates that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the performance of alternative learning methods, such as Random Forest and Support Vector Machines, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
